column1: 007 - The Living Daylights (Europe)>007 - The Living Daylights>1987>ESRB - RP (Rating Pending)>Domark Software Ltd.>Walking Circles>Arcade\Run & Gun>3.4.png>1 Player>"A ""James Bond"" action/arcade game based on the movie with the same name. Your aim is to avenge the death of Felix Leiter
column2: who was killed by the drug baron Sanchez.****Technically the game consists of several different vertical scrolling action sequences. In each stage you must fly
column3: drive or walk through a preset terrain. While doing that
column5: avoid their shots and collect items (mainly ammunition). Some levels rely more on shooting

column1: 10th Frame (Europe)>10th Frame>1986>ESRB - RP (Rating Pending)>U.S. Gold Ltd.>Access Software Inc.>Sports\Bowling>3.0.png>1-8 Players>Leader Board authors Bruce and Roger Carver tried their hand at tenpin bowling
column2: in one of the game's earliest recreations. The process of bowling the ball involves timing a succession of clicks to set the right angle
column3: speed and curve
column4: similarly to Leaderboard's system. Three skill levels are provided - Kids level sets the speed and hook automatically
column5: while Amateur has more margin for error with hook/slice than professional. The game is played from a plan view
column6: with four other (empty) lanes visible. Single matches or a league structure can be played.

1942 (Europe)>1942>1986>ESRB - RP (Rating Pending)>Elite Systems Ltd.>Capcom Co. Ltd.>Shoot'em Up\V-Scrolling>3.3.png>1-2 Players>"A conversion of the arcade game
column2: 1942 is a vertically scrolling shooter for one or two players. The year is 1942
column3: and you are a daring fighter pilot ""Super Ace"". You begin and end each of the numerous levels on an aircraft carrier and then fly your plane into battle against the enemy over both sea and land. After destroying certain plane formations you can collect several different power ups to increase your fire power and chances of survival."

column1: 1943 - The Battle of Midway (Europe)>1943 - The Battle of Midway>1987>ESRB - RP (Rating Pending)>Capcom Co. Ltd.>Capcom Co. Ltd.>Shoot'em Up\V-Scrolling>3.5.png>1-2 Players>The sequel to 1942
column2: which is still a vertically scrolling shooter
column3: has the player once again fighting over the clouds during the second world war
column4: this time in an intense battle just off the coast of Midway islands.****Updates to the gameplay include an energy bar
column5: which can be run down by either being hit from incoming fire or using a special weapon. The energy bar can be replenished by picking up power-ups
column7: cyclones and waves) can knock down all fighters on the screen at the time.

column1: 1st Division Manager (Europe)>1st Division Manager>1992>ESRB - RP (Rating Pending)>Codemasters>Codemasters>Simulation\Soccer>3.3.png>1 Player>1st Division Manager is a football management game where you take on a team of your choice in any of the top four English leagues. On the main menu there are four icons as well as some major information such as your name
column3: your current league position
column4: a rating and the account balance. The first icon from left is the picture of a computer and by clicking on it you will get to the main database menu where you can handle the playersâ€™ training
column5: studying the coming fixtures and edit the teams or players. The second icon is a telephone. Press it and you will be able to make a phone call to either the Transfer Market (for buying and selling players) or the the Bank (to get a loan). The third icon is a note book and by clicking on it you will see tables from all four divisions. The last icon is the picture of a football pitch and by pressing it you will get to your next match. After choosing your squad you will see the highlights of the match from a top-down perspective. After match you will get reports about players being injured
column6: results in the other matches and the finances for that week.

column1: 2 Player Soccer Squad (Europe)>2 Player Soccer Squad>1990>ESRB - RP (Rating Pending)>Cult>D & H Games>Simulation\Soccer>3.3.png>1 Player>Most football management games written for 64K/48K computers concentrated their memory space on providing as many features as possible for a lone player. As the title implies
column2: this game is an exception - 2 players each take control of a club
column3: taking it in turns to make their managerial decisions and play their matches. For an extra competitive edge
column4: they can include their own name among the players (which are otherwise made up of the real players of the day).****The game uses a fictional 20-team superleague
column6: as well as a knock-out cup. You can buy or sell players
column7: who have ability ratings out of 15
column8: and swap your squad of 19 around to choose 11 starters plus 2 substitutes. Match scores are listed along with goalscorers
column9: although the scorers update more quickly than the scores. You are kept up to date with financial changes after each match.

3D Starstrike (Europe)>3D Starstrike>1984>ESRB - RP (Rating Pending)>Realtime Software Ltd.>Realtime Games Software Ltd.>Shoot'em Up\3D>4.3.png>1 Player>The Outsiders have attacked the Earth Federation
column2: laying waste to its defense fleets. In desperation
column3: Federation Command sends the new Starstrike space fighters to attack the Outsiders's main bases (which are converted moons)
column4: hoping to exploit a fatal flaw in the design: a direct hit to the reactor at the center of the base might lead to its destruction.****Both regarding graphics and gameplay
column5: 3D Starstrike is essentially a clone of Atari's Star Wars. Using wireframe graphics with a first-person perspective
column6: the player controls the Starstrike fighter in several distinct phases: the first phase is the approach to the enemy base
column7: where Outsider space fighters must be destroyed. The second phase takes place close to the surface of the base
column8: where enemy bunkers and laser towers await. The third phase is a trench run
column9: where gun turrets await at the side of the trench
column10: and catwalks blocking the way must be dogded. The run culminates in the reactor room
column11: where two reactor pods must be hit to destroy the base.****After a base is destroyed
column12: the game continues with a new base in the next level
column13: with later levels having a higher difficulty.
